channel.title: No-Ip; Help!
channel.description:
OK here's the deal. I have recently been updating my Project Czar server source and I got my server up for like 5 days straight about a 2 weeks ago. Now, I portforwarded and everything, made my no-ip (flamerealm.no-ip.org) downloaded the No-Ip DUC and could get lots of ppl on but now for some reason, even I can't connect to it using my no-ip.
I open the duc and start my server like I have been doing, but it doesn't work anymore. I used RuneLocus's server status and it always comes up with the server offline.
Please if anyone can give any advice in to my situation I would appreciate it greatly. :D ;) :D

item.title: No-Ip; Help!
item.dc:creator: @jc22493 Jc22493
item.description:
@jc22493 wrote:

Try using a different source (not Project Czar), because that sometimes happens to me when I use Czar. If the other source works, then the problem is Czar. If it does not work either, check you PATH and CLASSPATH, for you may have downloaded a newer update of Java.

Hope I helped and GOOD LUCK!
